                            <comment id="17618965" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2022 15:41:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CVE-2022-42004 looks like we can suppress:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In FasterXML jackson-databind before 2.13.4, resource exhaustion can occur because of a lack of a check in BeanDeserializer._deserializeFromArray to prevent use of deeply nested arrays. An application is vulnerable only with certain customized choices for deserialization.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CVE-2022-42003 looks quite similar:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In FasterXML jackson-databind before 2.14.0-rc1, resource exhaustion can occur because of a lack of a check in primitive value deserializers to avoid deep wrapper array nesting, when the UNWRAP_SINGLE_VALUE_ARRAYS feature is enabled. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think either of these are worth upgrading for and I&apos;m not keen on upgrading to an RC version anyway, so patches to suppress:&lt;/p&gt;

