                            <comment id="17619648" author="smiklosovic" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2022 15:21:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Given this just suppresses CVE and doesn&apos;t have any impact on the code as such, I am +1 even though CI runs are quite ugly but what I saw it is mostly just flakies and timeouts in action.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17619661" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2022 15:40:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17899959" author="kaps_11" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2024 08:26:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20093&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20093&lt;/a&gt; is marked as duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17966&quot; title=&quot;jackson-databind vulnerability CVE-2022-42003 CVE-2022-42004&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17966&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-17966&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but the issue is not fixed , we still see the old version jackson-databind2.13.2.2 in Cassandra 5.0.2. Could you please let us know if there will be a&#160; new version of this jar available in the forthcoming releases or is Cassandra not vulnerable to the following CVE&apos;s in jackson-databind2.13.2.2 .jar&lt;/p&gt;

