&lt;p&gt;This will result in a StackOverflowError:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;NoHostAvailable: (&apos;Unable to complete the operation against any hosts&apos;, {&amp;lt;Host: 127.0.0.1:9042 datacenter1&amp;gt;: &amp;lt;Error from server: code=0000 [Server error] message=&quot;java.lang.StackOverflowError&quot;&amp;gt;})&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The stack trace is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;{{&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;ERROR &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Native-Transport-Requests-1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; 2025-09-07 18:53:05,983 ExceptionHandlers.java:240 - Unexpected exception during request; channel = &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;id: 0xb150addf, L:/127.0.0.1:9042 - R:/127.0.0.1:60108&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;java.lang.StackOverflowError: null&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.core.json.JsonReadContext.createChildArrayContext(JsonReadContext.java:130)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.core.json.ReaderBasedJsonParser.nextToken(ReaderBasedJsonParser.java:752)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.UntypedObjectDeserializer$Vanilla.deserialize(UntypedObjectDeserializer.java:720)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.UntypedObjectDeserializer$Vanilla.mapArray(UntypedObjectDeserializer.java:880)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.UntypedObjectDeserializer$Vanilla.deserialize(UntypedObjectDeserializer.java:737)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.UntypedObjectDeserializer$Vanilla.mapArray(UntypedObjectDeserializer.java:880)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.UntypedObjectDeserializer$Vanilla.deserialize(UntypedObjectDeserializer.java:737)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.UntypedObjectDeserializer$Vanilla.mapArray(UntypedObjectDeserializer.java:880)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;...&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.Json.parseJson(Json.java:273)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.Json$Literal.prepareAndCollectMarkers(Json.java:68)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.statements.UpdateStatement$ParsedInsertJson.prepareInternal(UpdateStatement.java:226)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.statements.ModificationStatement$Parsed.prepare(ModificationStatement.java:960)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.statements.ModificationStatement$Parsed.prepare(ModificationStatement.java:948)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.statements.ModificationStatement$Parsed.prepare(ModificationStatement.java:923)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.QueryProcessor.getStatement(QueryProcessor.java:911)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#0747a6&quot;&gt;&#160; at org.apache.cassandra.cql3.QueryProcessor.parse(QueryProcessor.java:347)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When testing the latest from v4 (4.1), and v5, the query receives an expected InvalidRequest error, so this only remains as affecting the latest v4.0 release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is the case that to trigger the exception, someone needs the ability to run the JSON parsing through the CQL interface. I am unsure if a readonly query could trigger the parsing without the deeply-nested content pre-existing in a column.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wanted to ask, given that the issue can be triggered from a query, is it still OK to suppress?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18019126" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2025 12:01:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suppose we could improve the error message on 4.0, though this is a pretty esoteric query most users won&apos;t hit.  In terms of damage, a user with write permission can do significantly more without this query, so I think suppressing is still ok.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smiklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smiklosovic&quot;&gt;smiklosovic&lt;/a&gt; WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18019148" author="smiklosovic" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2025 12:49:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; this will be auto-resolved when somebody releases 4.0.19. We have bumped Jackson there to 2.19.2 , tracked by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20848&quot; title=&quot;jackson-core vulnerability: CVE-2025-52999&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20848&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20848&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18019219" author="JIRAUSER310916" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2025 19:47:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That sounds good, so then the suppress/not-suppress is moot with 4.0.19, since then 4.0/4.1/5.0 are all using jackson-databind versions without the vulnerability. And also +1 that there&apos;s no additional risk for a user with write beyond the existing trust/risk already conveyed. I could not find any way to trigger via a pure-read path, and also could not find a way from reading the code. (yet, a poor proof by lack of counter evidence)&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
